# .trivyignore
# This file contains a strict list of unavoidable vulnerabilities that Trivy should ignore.
# DO NOT add CVEs here unless they meet the following criteria:
# 1. The vulnerability originates from a base OS package (e.g., glibc, kernel components).
# 2. The upstream maintainer (e.g., Debian Security Team) has marked it as "Will Not Fix" 
#    or "No Patch Available".
# 3. There is no viable mitigation strategy.
#
# FORMAT:
# <CVE-ID> # <Justification and link to upstream tracker>
#
# EXAMPLE:
# CVE-2023-XXXXX # Ignored by Debian: https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2023-XXXXX
